# 🚗 Car Details Data Science Capstone Project

## 📌 Objective
The objective of this project is to perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on the Car Details dataset and build a Machine Learning model to predict car prices based on various features.

---

## 📂 Dataset
- Dataset: Car Details Dataset
- Contains information such as:
  - Car Name
  - Year
  - Selling Price
  - Present Price
  - Fuel Type
  - Seller Type
  - Transmission
  - Owner

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Scikit-learn
- Streamlit
- GitHub

---

## 🔄 Steps Performed

### 1. Data Exploration
- Analyzed dataset structure using Excel & Python
- Generated summary statistics

### 2. Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
- Handled missing values
- Performed encoding (One-Hot Encoding)
- Applied feature scaling where required

### 3. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Visualized relationships between variables
- Created graphs using Matplotlib & Seaborn
- Derived meaningful insights

### 4. Feature Engineering
- Selected important features for modeling
- Prepared dataset for training

### 5. Machine Learning Modeling
- Applied multiple models:
  - Linear Regression
  - Decision Tree
  - Random Forest
- Compared models using evaluation metrics

### 6. Model Evaluation
- Used metrics like:
  - R² Score
  - Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
  - Mean Squared Error (MSE)
- Selected best performing model

### 7. Model Saving & Loading
- Saved trained model
- Loaded model for prediction

### 8. Testing
- Created a sample dataset (20 records)
- Tested model performance on new data

### 9. Deployment
- Built a web app using Streamlit
- Deployed model for public access

---

## 📊 Key Insights
- Newer cars have higher selling prices
- Fuel type affects car pricing
- Owner count impacts resale value
- Automatic cars tend to have higher prices

